Let's see
what they're up to now.

00:13:19,053 --> 00:13:20,655
King:
After returning home

00:13:20,655 --> 00:13:23,291
as an army‐intelligence officer
with two deployments to Iraq,

00:13:23,291 --> 00:13:26,460
I was completely floored
by the condition my town was in.

00:13:26,460 --> 00:13:29,063
This area has one of
the highest addiction

00:13:29,063 --> 00:13:31,032
and overdose rates
in the country.

00:13:31,032 --> 00:13:32,800
I wanted to start something
that would be able

00:13:32,800 --> 00:13:34,602
to give back
to my hometown.

00:13:34,602 --> 00:13:36,737
Wallace: We have now grown
into 30 different products,

00:13:36,737 --> 00:13:39,240
and we are a complete
grooming and skin‐care line.

00:13:39,240 --> 00:13:40,575
When we pitched
to the Sharks,

00:13:40,575 --> 00:13:43,678
we had only done
$56,000 in sales.

00:13:43,678 --> 00:13:45,580
Now, less than
three years later,

00:13:45,580 --> 00:13:48,816
we're totaling $1.7 million
in sales.

00:13:48,816 --> 00:13:50,585
Everything going alright?
Going great.

00:13:50,585 --> 00:13:53,487
One of the most difficult things
for people in recovery

00:13:53,487 --> 00:13:55,389
is finding employment
after treatment.

00:13:55,389 --> 00:13:57,925
We began to hire people
who had completed treatment,

00:13:57,925 --> 00:14:00,127
and then we began
to notice incredible

00:14:00,127 --> 00:14:01,829
positive changes
in their lives.

00:14:01,829 --> 00:14:03,264
Now they're getting
apartments,

00:14:03,264 --> 00:14:05,333
they're regaining custody
of their children.

00:14:05,333 --> 00:14:08,736
It's just an amazingly
beautiful thing to be a part of.

00:14:08,736 --> 00:14:11,772
We made the commitment
that our entire labor force

00:14:11,772 --> 00:14:13,774
will be made of people
in recovery.

00:14:13,774 --> 00:14:16,177
<i>I think people want to be</i>
<i>part of something,</i>

00:14:16,177 --> 00:14:19,480
<i>especially if the mission is</i>
<i>solid and they believe in it.</i>

00:14:19,480 --> 00:14:22,116
<i>I know you're going to bleed</i>
<i>for this to help the people</i>

00:14:22,116 --> 00:14:24,652
<i>that depend on you guys,</i>
<i>and I love that.</i>

00:14:24,652 --> 00:14:26,988
Herjavec: Doc Spartan started
in a small town in Ohio,

00:14:26,988 --> 00:14:28,422
doing everything themselves,

00:14:28,422 --> 00:14:32,260
and still doing it themselves
in a small town in‐house.

00:14:32,260 --> 00:14:33,661
You can start from nothing,

00:14:33,661 --> 00:14:35,763
and you can create
any kind of a business.

00:14:36,964 --> 00:14:39,100
Along with the success
of our business,

00:14:39,100 --> 00:14:41,502
it's just amazing
how far our town has come.

00:14:41,502 --> 00:14:44,305
King: We've seen over 10 new
businesses open up downtown.

00:14:44,305 --> 00:14:45,940
If we can do it here,

00:14:45,940 --> 00:14:48,943
other people can do it
within their own communities.

00:14:48,943 --> 00:14:51,512
One of the biggest lessons
the military teaches you is

00:14:51,512 --> 00:14:53,681
to leave it better
than you found it.

00:14:53,681 --> 00:14:55,549
And it's been
that guiding principle

00:14:55,549 --> 00:14:57,618
that's helped us here
in our hometown.

00:14:57,618 --> 00:14:58,886
Whoo!

00:14:58,886 --> 00:15:01,122
This is our mission
and our legacy.

00:15:01,122 --> 00:15:03,557
I've never been more proud
of Portsmouth,

00:15:03,557 --> 00:15:06,394
but I'm really excited
for what the future brings.

